res.status(201).json(...)

👉 Confirms success

🔐 Why bcrypt?
❌ Without bcrypt
{
  "password": "123456"
}

👉 Anyone can see password → VERY DANGEROUS
✅ With bcrypt
{
  "password": "$2b$10$XyZ..."
}

👉 Impossible to reverse
🧠 What 10 Means?
bcrypt.hash(password, 10)

👉 Salt rounds (security level)
Higher = more secure but slower

